Definition: Attribute between a SpatialImage entity and a CoordinateSpace entity that is used to associate spatial metadata with a physical file.
Integer associated with a particular cluster as specified in the clusterLabelsMap.
A map whose value at each location denotes cluster membership. Each cluster is denoted by a different integer.
Example: file:///path/to/cluster_labels.img

Definition: Number of vertices that make up the cluster.
Number of voxels that make up the cluster.
Statistic defined at the cluster-level in an excusion set. In SPM it is defined as the cluster size.
Domain or Attributes: clusterSizeInVoxels, clusterLabelId, clusterSizeInResels, pValueUncorrected, pValueFWER, qValueFDR
Example:
entity(niiri:cluster_0001,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ClusterStatistic',
    prov:label = "Cluster Statistic: 0001" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:clusterSizeInVoxels = "530" %% xsd:int,
    nidm:clusterLabelId = "1",
    spm:clusterSizeInResels = "23.1209189500945" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueUncorrected = "9.56276736481136e-52" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueFWER = "0" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:qValueFDR = "7.65021389184909e-51" %% xsd:float])

Definition: Inference testing for the joint significance of all effects.
The process of estimating a contrast from the estimated parameters of statistical model.
Example:
activity(niiri:contrast_estimation_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ContrastEstimation',
    prov:label = "Contrast estimation"])

Definition: A map whose value at each location is statistical contrast estimate.
Example:
entity(niiri:contrast_map_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ContrastMap',
    prov:location = "file:///path/to/con_0001.img" %% xsd:anyURI,
    prov:label = "Contrast Map: listening > rest" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:contrastName = "listening > rest" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:originalFileName = "con_0001.img" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:coordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
    crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])

Definition: Name of the contrast.
Example: "Listening > Rest"

Definition: A map whose value at each location is the standard error of a given contrast.
Example:
entity(niiri:contrast_standard_error_map_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ContrastStandardErrorMap',
    prov:location = "file:///path/to/contrastSE.nii" %% xsd:anyURI,
    prov:label = "Contrast Standard Error Map" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:originalFileName = "contrastSE.nii" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:coordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
    crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])

Definition: Vector defining the linear combination associated with a particular contrast.
Example:
"entity(niiri:t_contrast_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:TContrastWeights',
    nidm:contrastName = ""listening > rest"" %% xsd:string,
    prov:label = ""Contrast: Listening > Rest"" %% xsd:string,
    prov:value = ""[1, 0, 0]"" %% xsd:string])"

model:
- search for coordinate uri
- subclasses of coordinate
- additional properties (e.g. units)
Definition: A point in N-dimensional space where the dimensions could be arbitrary.
Domain or Attributes: coordinate1, coordinate1InUnits, coordinate2, coordinate2InUnits, coordinate3, coordinate3InUnits
Example: 3D (x,y,x), 2D (x,y), Vertices, etc.

Definition: Coordinate along the first dimension in voxels.
Coordinate along the first dimension in voxel units.
Coordinate along the second dimension in voxels.
Coordinate along the second dimension in voxel units.
Coordinate along the third dimension in voxels.
Coordinate along the third dimension in voxel units
An entity with spatial attributes (e.g., dimensions, units, and voxel-to-world mapping) that provides context to a SpatialImage (e.g., a StatisticMap).
Domain or Attributes: voxelToWorldMapping, voxelUnits, voxelSize, coordinateSystem, numberOfDimensions, dimensions
Example:
entity(niiri:coordinate_space_id_1,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:CoordinateSpace',
    prov:label = "Coordinate space 1" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:voxelToWorldMapping = "[[-3, 0, 0, 78],[0, 3, 0, -112],[0, 0, 3, -50],[0, 0, 0, 1]]" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:voxelUnits = "['mm', 'mm', 'mm']" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:voxelSize = "[3, 3, 3]" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:coordinateSystem = 'nidm:mniCoordinateSystem',
    nidm:numberOfDimensions = "3" %% xsd:int,
    nidm:dimensions = "[53,63,46]" %% xsd:string])

Definition: Type of coordinate system.
Example: nidm:MniCoordinateSystem

Definition: "A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn."
Synonym note: This definition is from NCIT. Please update this note if the definition is modified.
Example:
entity(niiri:data_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:Data',
    prov:type = 'prov:Collection',
    prov:label = "Data" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:grandMeanScaling = "true" %%xsd:boolean,
    nidm:targetIntensity = "100" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:intraMaskMedian = "115.32" %% xsd:float])

Definition: A matrix of values defining the explanatory variables used in a regression model.  Each column corresponds to one explanatory variable, each row corresponds to one observation.
Example:
entity(niiri:design_matrix_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:DesignMatrix',
    prov:location = "file:///path/to/design_matrix.csv" %% xsd:anyURI,
    nidm:visualisation = "file:///path/to/design_matrix.png" %% xsd:anyURI,
    prov:label = "Design Matrix" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:originalFileName = "design_matrix.csv" %% xsd:string])

Definition: Dimensions of some N-dimensional data.
Degrees of freedom of the effect.
Statistic value transformed into Z units; the output of a process which takes a non-normal statistic and transforms it to an equivalent z score.
Degrees of freedom of the error.
Set of map elements surviving a thresholding procedure.
Example:
entity(niiri:excursion_set_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ExcursionSet',
    prov:location = "file:///path/to/thresh_spmT_0001.img" %% xsd:anyURI,
    prov:label = "Excursion Set" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:clusterLabelsMap = "file:///path/to/cluster_labels.img" %% xsd:anyURI,
    spm:maximumIntensityProjection = "file:///path/to/MIP.png" %% xsd:anyURI,
    nidm:originalFileName = "thresh_spmT_0001.img" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:coordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
    crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])

Definition: A numerical value that establishes a bound on a range of cluster-sizes. / [from extentThresh:]        Minimum cluster size used when thresholding a statistic image        5voxels
Example:
entity(niiri:extent_threshold_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ExtentThreshold',
    prov:label = "Extent Threshold: k>=0" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:clusterSizeInVoxels = "0" %% xsd:float,
    spm:clusterSizeInResels = "0" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueUncorrected = "1" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueFWER = "1" %% xsd:float])

Definition: The statistic from the F-test, a test of the hypothesis that the standard deviations of two normally distributed populations are equal, and thus that they are of comparable origin.
Contrast based on an F-statistic.
A map whose value at each location is an F-statistic.
A numerical value that establishes a bound on a range of voxelwise or vertex-wise defined statistic.
Example:
entity(niiri:height_threshold_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:HeightThreshold',
    prov:label = "Height Threshold: p<0.05 (FWE)" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:userSpecifiedThresholdType = "p-value FWE" %% xsd:string,
    prov:value = "5.23529984739211" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueUncorrected = "7.62276079258051e-07" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueFWER = "0.05" %% xsd:float])

Definition: The process of inferring the excursion set from a statistical map.
Example:
activity(niiri:inference_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:Inference',
    prov:label = "Inference"])

Definition: Inference in which the critical area of a distribution is one-sided so that it is either greater than or less than a certain value, but not both. (from "one-tailed test" in investopedia)
Example:
activity(niiri:inference_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:InferenceOneTailed',
    prov:label = "Inference"])

Definition: Inference in which the critical area of a distribution is two sided and tests whether a sample is either greater than or less than a certain range of values. (from "two-tailed test" in investopedia)
Example:
activity(niiri:inference_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:InferenceTwoTailed',
    prov:label = "Inference"])

Definition: 2D or 3D structured dataset.
map or surface on which the associated results are displayed.
Example:
entity(niiri:mask_id_2,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:MaskMap',
    prov:location = "file:///path/to/mask.img" %% xsd:anyURI,
    prov:label = "Mask" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:originalFileName = "mask.img" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:atCoordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
    crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])

Definition: Coordinate system defined with reference to the MNI atlas.
The process of estimating the parameters of a general linear model from the available data.
Example:
activity(niiri:model_pe_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ModelParametersEstimation',
    prov:label = "Model parameters estimation"])

Definition: Estimated Full Width at Half Maximum of the noise distribution.
Domain or Attributes: <only child of are used in the data model>

Definition: Number of dimensions of a data matrix.
Original name associated with a file (without path) in the context of the analysis software package.
Example: con_0001.img

Definition: A map whose value at each location is the estimate of a model parameter.
Example:
entity(niiri:parameter_estimate_map_id_1,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ParameterEstimateMap',
    prov:location = "file:///path/to/beta_0001.img" %% xsd:anyURI,
    prov:label = "Beta Map 1" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:originalFileName = "beta_0001.img" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:atCoordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
    crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])

Definition: Statistic defined at the peak-level in an excursion set.
Example:
entity(niiri:peak_0001,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:PeakStatistic',
    prov:label = "Peak Statistic: 0001" %% xsd:string,
    prov:location = 'niiri:coordinate_0001',
    prov:value = "13.9346199035645" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:equivalentZStatistic = "999999999" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueUncorrected = "4.44089209850063e-16" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:pValueFWER = "0" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:qValueFDR = "6.3705194444993e-11" %% xsd:float])

Definition: "A quantitative confidence value that represents the probability of obtaining a result at least as extreme as that actually obtained, assuming that the actual value was the result of chance alone."
Synonym note: This definition is from OBI. Please update this note if the definition is modified.

Definition: "A quantitative confidence value resulting from a multiple testing error correction method which adjusts the p-value used as input to control for Type I error in the context of multiple pairwise tests"
Synonym note: This definition is from OBI. Please update this note if the definition is modified.

Definition: A p-value reported without correction for multiple testing.
P-value adjusted for the multiple testing, controlling for the False Discovery Rate
Is the random field assumed to be stationary across the entire search volume?
Example: stationaryRandomField

Definition: A map whose value at each location is the residual of the mean squares fit to the data.
Example:
entity(niiri:residual_mean_squares_map_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:ResidualMeanSquaresMap',
    prov:location = "file:///path/to/ResMS.img" %% xsd:anyURI,
    prov:label = "Residual Mean Squares Map" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:originalFileName = "ResMS.img" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:atCoordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
    crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])
synonyms and related urls: This is a map of "residuals" as defined at http://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/STATO/?p=classes&conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fpurl.obolibrary.org%2Fobo%2FSTATO_0000234

Definition: Full width at half maximum of a Gaussian smoothing kernel in real world units (e.g. mm mm mm).
Name and number that specifies the software version.
Example: SPM99, SPM2, SPM5, SPM8, SPM12b, FSL5.0.0

Definition: Statistical Parametric Mapping software package for the analysis of neuroimaging data from the FIL Methods Group.
FMRIB Software Library software package for the analysis of neuroimaging data from the FMRIB.

"A quantitative confidence value which is the standard deviations of the sample in a frequency distribution, obtained by dividing the standard deviation by the total number of cases in the frequency distribution."
Synonym note: This definition is from OBI. Please update this note if the definition is modified.

Definition: Random-field that is constant across the search volume.
A map whose value at each location is a statistic.

Example:
entity(niiri:statistical_map_id,

    prov:label = "Statistical Map: listening > rest" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:contrastName = "listening > rest" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:originalFileName = "spmT_0001.img" %% xsd:string,
    nidm:errorDegreesOfFreedom = "72.9999999990787" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:effectDegreesOfFreedom = "1" %% xsd:float,
    nidm:atCoordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
    crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])

Definition: Contrast based on a t-statistic.
Example:
entity(niiri:t_contrast_id,
    [prov:type = 'nidm:TContrastWeights',
    nidm:contrastName = "listening > rest" %% xsd:string,
    prov:label = "Contrast: Listening > Rest" %% xsd:string,
    prov:value = "[1, 0, 0]" %% xsd:string])

Definition: A map whose value at each location is a T-statistic value.
Domain or Attributes: prov:location, contrastName, originalFileName, errorDegreesOfFreedom, effectDegreesOfFreedom, atCoordinateSpace, crypto:sha512

Definition: Map or surface on which the associated results are displayed.
Example: MNI152.nii.gz or cortex.surf.gii

Definition: Type (p-value either corrected or uncorrected or statistic) of the user-defined height threshold
Example: nidm:pValueFWER

Definition: Graphical representation of an entity.
Example: file:///path/to/design_matrix.png

Definition: 3D size of a voxel measured in voxelUnits.
Voxel to World Mapping. Change-of-basis matrix from the voxel to world space?
Units associated with each dimensions of some N-dimensional data.
Number of resels that make up a cluster.
Expected number of clusters in an excursion set.
Expected number of vertices in a cluster.
Expected number of voxels in a cluster.
Peak statistic threshold corrected for false discovery rate at a level of alpha = 0.05.
Peak statistic threshold corrected for family-wise error at a level of alpha = 0.05.
Inference testing for the joint significance of a subset of the effects.
Maximum intensity projection of a map.

Definition: Estimated Full Width at Half Maximum of the noise distribution in world units.
Estimated Full Width at Half Maximum of the noise distribution in world vertices.
Estimated Full Width at Half Maximum of the noise distribution in voxels.
synonyms and related urls: Synonyms of or close match with nidm:NoiseFWHM

Definition: Random field that is variable across the search volume.
Example: <this is an attribute value>

Definition: Size of one resel in voxels or vertices.
A map whose value at each location is the number of resels per voxel.
Example:
entity(niiri:resels_per_voxel_map_id,
      [prov:type = 'spm:ReselsPerVoxelMap',
      prov:location = "file:///path/to/RPV.img" %% xsd:anyURI,
      prov:label = "Resels per Voxel Map" %% xsd:string,
      nidm:originalFileName = "RPV.img" %% xsd:string,
      nidm:atCoordinateSpace = 'niiri:coordinate_space_id_1',
      crypto:sha512 = "e43b6e01b0463fe7d40782137867a..." %% xsd:string])

Definition: Total number of product of coordinate units within the search volume.
Total number of resels within the search volume.
Total number of vertices within the search volume.
Total number of voxels within the search volume.

Description of geometry of search volume.  As per Worsley et al. [ http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20408186 ], the first element is the Euler Characteristic of the search volume, the second element is twice the average caliper diameter, the third element is half the surface area, and the fourth element is the volume.  With the exception of the first element (which is a unitless integer) all quantities are in units of Resels.
Range: Vector of 1 positive integer and 3 positive floats

Definition: Statistic defined at the set-level in an excusion set. In SPM it is defined as the number of clusters above a given size in an excursion set.
Example:
entity(niiri:set_statistic_id,
      [prov:type = 'spm:SetStatistic',
      prov:label = "Set Statistic" %% xsd:string,
      prov:value = "8" %% xsd:int,
      nidm:pValue = "8.95949980872501e-14" %% xsd:float])

Smallest cluster size in voxels significant at family-wise error corrected alpha value of 0.05.
revision number of a piece of software.

Definition: Binary flag defining whether the data was scaled. Specifically, "grand mean scaling" refers to multipliciation of every voxel in every scan by a common value.  Grand mean scaling is essential for first-level fMRI, to transform the arbitrary MRI units, but is generally not used with second level analyses.
Example: TRUE

Definition: Value to which the grand mean of the Data was scaled (applies only if grandMeanScaling is true).
Median value considering only in-mask voxels. Useful diagnostic when computed on grand mean image when grandMeanScaling is TRUE, as the median should be close to targetIntensity.
mask defined by the user to restrain the space in which model fitting is performed.
Example:
entity(niiri:mask_id_1,

Definition: Centre Of Gravity for the cluster, equivalent to the concept of Centre Of Gravity for a object with distributed mass, where intensity substitutes for mass in this case (definition from http://fsl.fmrib.ox.ac.uk/fsl/fslwiki/Cluster)
Example:
entity(niiri:center_of_gravity_1,
        [prov:type = 'fsl:centerOfGravity',
        prov:label = "Center of gravity 1",
        prov:location = 'niiri:COG_coordinate_0001'])
